<section xml:id="ss-Templates_review" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
	<title>Templates</title>

	<introduction>
		<p>
			Templates are used to write equations from given or calculated information, to read constants from the equations, or simply to identify the type of equation in order to use type-specific formulas or information.
		</p>
	</introduction>
	<p>
		<term>Linear equation template:</term> <m>\text{dep}=\text{start}+\text{slope}\ast\text{indep}</m>
	</p>

	<p>
		<term>Power equation template:</term> <m>\text{dep} = k \ast \text{indep}^{n}</m>
	</p>

	<p>
		<term>Quadratic equation template:</term> <m>\text{dep} = a \ast \text{indep}^2 + b \ast\text{indep} + c</m>
	</p>

	<p>
		<term>Exponential equation template:</term> <m>\text{dep} = \text{start} \ast \text{growth factor} ^ {\text{indep}}</m>
	</p>
